\textbf{Mr Tan is organising a family movie night. He bought a large pizza and cut it into 12 equal slices. During the night, his children ate } \frac{8}{12} \text{ of the pizza.} \\ 

\text{If Mr Tan wants to share the remaining pizza equally among his 4 friends the next day, what fraction of the whole pizza will each friend get?} \\ 
\text{Express your answer in its simplest form.}

response_dict.solution:
\textbf{Step 1: Find the amount of pizza left after the children ate.} \\ 
\text{Total pizza} = 1 \\ 
\text{Fraction eaten} = \frac{8}{12} \\ 
\text{Fraction left} = 1 - \frac{8}{12} = \frac{12}{12} - \frac{8}{12} = \frac{4}{12} = \frac{1}{3} 
\\
\textbf{Step 2: Divide the remaining pizza among 4 friends.}
\\
\text{Each friend gets } \frac{1}{3} \div 4 = \frac{1}{3} \times \frac{1}{4} = \frac{1}{12} \text{ of the pizza}
\\
\textbf{Final Answer:}

\boxed{\frac{1}{12}}

\text{Each friend will get } \frac{1}{12} \text{ of the whole pizza.}

